-height: 26px; margin: 0;">The Founder(s).&nbsp;</p></li></ol><p style=3D"c=
olor: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Of t=
hese three, the Founder is the most important. The idea may change, and the=
 market may not even exist yet. If it does, it&#8217;s likely full of unwel=
coming incumbents looking to beat the new entrant out of business. A great =
Founder can overcome those obstacles, evolving the idea based on customer f=
eedback while staying true to the vision, willing a market into being, and =
fighting for their big piece of it.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; fo=
nt-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Ian Janicki is the pe=
rfect Founder for Outfit. A second-generation architect, Ian grew up in the=
 trades, working construction as a teenager before studying at the nation&#=
8217;s top undergrad architecture program, Cornell.&nbsp;</p><div class=3D"=
